! GARP Field Description File (FDF) Template
!
! Field: Best (4 layer) K Index (C).
!
! *** Required Parameters ***
type			= scalar
layer                   = n
function		= sub(add(add(dwpc@850,dwpc@700),sub(tmpc@850,tmpc@500)),tmpc@700)
description		= K Index. Values over 30 increase heavy rain threat \
                        = /with values over 36 a high threat and over 40 a \
                        = \ very high threat.  Note that the K Index is tied \
                        = \ to moisture at 700mb.  The NGM is a wetter model \
                        = \ than the Eta so expect the NGM to have higher \
                        = \ values.  This does not necessarily mean the NGM \
                        = \ is forecasting a greater risk.  Use this parameter \
                        = \ only in conjuction with others.
! *** End of Required Parameters ***
!
